 In support to our community Volunteers the team provide Group-based and Household based awareness sensitization (Such as Men’s, women’s and youth Groups  on GBV prevention  and available services

we carried out 3 hours focused Group Discussion on GBV,  Gender and Human Rights  , we  targeted women and girls  , including the current women groups , police officers and teachers , it was aimed  to shed light on  gender diversity and how gender Couse GBV to our community ,
in line with universal  standrd we provided comprehensive Medication  to   4 pysicall assault  .1 attempted rape  and 1 rape case
we provided  inclusive psychosocial support and counseling to  4, pysical assault,  1 attempted Rape  and 1 rape case

The team carried out   community awareness raising on the implication and dangers of FGM at waberi village , Noting that this  is a culture that’s richly in  train  with in the  community we opted to have 3 hours discussion  so that the community able to understand  what’s  FGM to them why we feel  it’s mistreatment on women’s rights

Reducing  the risk factors of GBV at the community , the team carried out  the monthly interactive  forums using walk in her shoes toolkit , it was 3 hours session and participants were selected from   wide range of people  with different professionals including , Health service providers , teachers , police officers, youth and the other community members , It  was mainly focusing on how we jointly increase community behavioral change practices and personal Accountability  , the session  started with a word prayer followed by introduction and later  emphasize the objective
112,  families were reched on GBV  prevention awareness sessions group discussion

We conducted 2 days training for local district officials, police officers, Active women groups, and the other community members; the team selected 40 participants as per the criteria, after welcoming   trainees to the training. Informing them that this module covers Gender Based Violence which is a critical issue that is often top of the list of cases reported at the police stations. The facilitator calls for active participation of everyone, Followed by   recitation of the Holy Quran, brief introduction, setting Ground rules,   Expectation of the participants and then highlighted the objective of our training. The facilitator  Explain to trainees that domestic violence negatively affects all aspects of our lives; participants had  varying beliefs about the factors that cause domestic violence.

After Introducing EMAP  to the community  the team begun recruiting  and implementing  the  women curriculum , we have selected 20 participants who express their interest in joining the sessions , the selected members include women groups from marginalized groups , community leaders, teachers and youth,  we have closely  work   the community leaders  for ensuring  proper selection is done in order to achieve   participants that  fully understand the  intervention .   After the selection process we launched the 1st , 2nd and the 3rd  week session for the women curriculum , the team identified space that feel safe and confidential for all ,  after warmly welcoming them,  the male facilitator  thank them for choosing to participate and their feedbacks ,  the male facilitator  was the one taking - over  the session by not dominating the female facilitator , we  govern   time , day and location for each meeting   and after spending discussion on the importance of women voices

Community nutrition workers and other nutrition workers will be tasked to undertake active case finding at community level through routine screening using the standard anthropocentric measures to detect acutely malnourished children and link them to nutrition sites for management. Program staff will screen at the site. Mass screening to be conducted quarterly will also aid in detection of cases. 22, 312 (5459 boys and 7897 girls, and 8956 PLWs) will be screened and appropriately referred under this activity in 3 fixed MCH/OTP and 4 mobile centers ( to the north, East ,South and West from the fixed MCH) in Beletweyne, Mataban, ans Jalalaqsi district of Hiran Region

Provide treatment of severe acute malnutrition to 649 (245 boys and 404 girls) children between age of 6-59 months through 3 fixed sites and 12 mobile outreach team.SAM cases will be refered to Mercy USA SC facilities.

Children attended to at the OTP with mild medical conditions will be treated at RRP health center and Primary Health care Center (PHC) and will be supported with hygiene promotion messages and the hygine kit distribution within the 1 fixed sites and 2 mobile sites.

Provision of the hygiene and hand washing kits that comprises soap for hand washing and personal hygiene, jerrycans, water treatment reagents aqua tabs to , (649 HH of both male and female, boys and girls)and PUR and 100% sanitary towel distribution for school going girls among the host communities and the IDPs. These are to the care givers of children with the SAM complication admitted to the facility.

Conduct integrated community and facility-based IYCF, health and hygiene promotion in the health facilities/ nutrition sites and at the community level. Nutrition workers including trained IYCF counselors and nutrition promoters will organize and conduct education sessions on IYCF, maternal nutrition and Nutrition health,hygiene promotion sessions targeting mothers and care takers of children between the ages of 6-59 months.2 sessions per site will be conducted per week per site targeting at least 20 persons thus care givers of children under the age of five years will be targeted for a period of 12 months.

10 staff 4 male and 6 female Staff (3 OTP nurses, 3 Screeners, trained on IMAM. staff working in the nutrition sites will be trained on integrated management  of acute malnutrition (IMAM). This will be a five day class room training with practical sessions.
13355 (5459 boys and 7897 girls)children receive bi- annual Vitamin A supplementation both at site and during community and EPI campaigns.
8956 Pregnant and lactating women receive multiple micro nutrients both at 1 fixed and 2 mobile site and community level.

8956 caregivers of malnourished children will receive information on IMAM programming and what to expect after treatment at OTP sites. This will be conducted at site by the nutrition promoters to all new caregivers.

10 staff 4 male and 6 female Staff and Community Health Workers/outreach workers trained on infant and young child feeding promotion and counseling including health and WASH practices. This will be a five day class room training with practical sessions.

One-day Mother led MUAC training will be done to 500 caregivers on the identification of malnutrition and ensure early action in treatment. This will be done by equipped nurses, community health workers in the target district of Hiran Region.

50 Staff, community committees and Community Health Workers/outreach workers trained on Nutrition health and hygiene promotion. This will be a three day class room training with practical sessions. who will further carry out hygiene promotion sessions reaching out to boys, girls, men and women in nutrition feeding centers, mosques and health facilities and schools, (1000HH of both male and female, boys and girls) HH to HH, door to door hygiene promotion sessions within the IDPs camp and Host community in the target districts in Hiran.
